 being distasteful to him and even of its frightening him off as naturally as it had appealed to my fancy.

I do not mean, by that, that I have ever had the least connection with the screen or the stage; in point of fact, the only time I performed was a score of years ago, in a little amateur affair at our squire’s country seat (which my father managed). I had to speak only a few words: “The prince bade me announce that he would be here presently. Ah! here he comes,” instead of which, full